WEBVTT

00:04.796 --> 00:06.548
<i>Quantum Leap was
an experimental</i>

00:06.548 --> 00:08.842
<i>time travel program
years away from being tested.</i>

00:08.842 --> 00:10.927
- Why did you leap?
- I don't remember anything.

00:10.927 --> 00:12.387
Your name is Dr. Ben Song.

00:12.387 --> 00:14.389
<i>You're a time traveler,
leaping from life to life</i>

00:14.389 --> 00:16.391
<i>trying to put right
what once went wrong.</i>

00:16.391 --> 00:18.226
Do you remember meeting
with this man?

00:18.226 --> 00:19.352
I lost time.

00:19.352 --> 00:20.353
Did you ever stop to think

00:20.353 --> 00:22.105
about who was behind the wheel?

00:22.105 --> 00:23.773
Are you kidding?
I keep drawing them.

00:23.773 --> 00:25.817
This is the person
you see in your dreams?

00:25.817 --> 00:27.235
<i>That's the person
who was behind the wheel</i>

00:27.235 --> 00:28.987
when I lost time.

00:28.987 --> 00:30.780
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:30.780 --> 00:34.451
<i>[upbeat Indian music]</i>

00:34.451 --> 00:38.371
<i>[singing in Hindi]</i>

00:38.371 --> 00:39.622
Where are the pakoras?

00:39.622 --> 00:40.749
Finishing now.

00:43.543 --> 00:45.378
- Dining room's ready.
- Almost 11:30.

00:45.378 --> 00:46.755
We're opening.
Let's go.

00:46.755 --> 00:48.465
- Awesome.
- Kamini,

00:48.465 --> 00:50.800
what are you doing looking
around happily <i>aise-vaise?</i>

00:50.800 --> 00:52.510
I need the tomatoes.

00:52.510 --> 00:53.303
Yes, Chef!

00:53.303 --> 00:54.429
"Yes, Chef"?

00:54.429 --> 00:55.680
Hit your head or what?

00:55.680 --> 00:57.015
How about, "Yes, Mummy."

00:57.015 --> 00:58.475
Right. Yes, Mummy.

00:58.475 --> 01:00.226
<i>Chalo.</i>
Put these outside.

01:00.226 --> 01:01.728
That smells great.

01:01.728 --> 01:02.771
Don't drool on it.

01:02.771 --> 01:04.647
I'll have to make it again.

01:04.647 --> 01:06.608
That way.

01:06.608 --> 01:09.069
<i>Hai Ram,</i> why did you give me
such useless daughters?

01:09.069 --> 01:10.070
- Rice!
- Rice.

01:10.070 --> 01:11.738
Don't forget the tongs.

01:11.738 --> 01:18.703
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:30.965 --> 01:32.384
Mmm.
Mm-hmm.

01:32.384 --> 01:33.718
I'm not gonna tell Mom,

01:33.718 --> 01:35.929
but you've gotta stop
eating the merchandise.

01:35.929 --> 01:37.263
Mm.
My bad.

01:37.263 --> 01:38.390
[laughs]
How many did you eat?

01:38.390 --> 01:39.849
- A lot.
- Oh.

01:39.849 --> 01:41.935
Finally realized
you have work today, Manisha?

01:41.935 --> 01:43.937
I was recipe testing.

01:43.937 --> 01:45.563
Remember?

01:45.563 --> 01:47.691
Today's the day.

01:47.691 --> 01:52.404
New dinner menu,
courtesy of Manisha Prasad.

01:52.404 --> 01:54.572
You said I could do it.

01:54.572 --> 01:57.033
- Did I?
- No, no backing out now.

01:57.033 --> 01:58.451
okay, I've got a whole plan.

01:58.451 --> 02:01.955
Dum biryani, masala prawns,
chana chaat.

02:01.955 --> 02:03.373
Dum biryani?

02:03.373 --> 02:04.958
Your father's favorite.

02:04.958 --> 02:06.084
[laughs softly]

02:06.084 --> 02:07.127
But do you really think
people are

02:07.127 --> 02:08.461
ready for that kind of food?

02:08.461 --> 02:10.797
I mean, it's
so unusual for them.

02:10.797 --> 02:12.841
Americans don't like
things they can't pronounce.

02:12.841 --> 02:14.134
I do.

02:14.134 --> 02:15.802
I know you're scared
about changing Dad's menu.

02:15.802 --> 02:19.472
But I think
this can really go well.

02:19.472 --> 02:22.142
<i>Didi</i> thinks so too, right?

02:22.142 --> 02:23.643
Oh, I'm <i>Didi.</i>

02:23.643 --> 02:25.311
Yeah, absolutely.

02:25.311 --> 02:26.980
You always take her side.

02:26.980 --> 02:28.314
[bell dings]

02:28.314 --> 02:30.108
- Hello. Welcome.
- Hi there.

02:30.108 --> 02:31.693
Try the pakoras.
They're fresh.

02:31.693 --> 02:33.153
And delicious.

02:33.153 --> 02:34.571
Right over here.
There's three of you?

02:34.571 --> 02:36.865
She doesn't always
take my side.

02:39.784 --> 02:42.078
First of all,
I'm--I'm very flattered.

02:42.078 --> 02:44.164
I didn't realize that you had

02:44.164 --> 02:46.708
a slightly concerning
artistic streak.

02:46.708 --> 02:49.419
Ian, we, uh, tracked down
the name Janis gave us

02:49.419 --> 02:51.129
of the person
who told Ben to leap.

02:51.129 --> 02:53.798
They're a barista at
a coffee shop in Silver Lake.

02:53.798 --> 02:55.717
- So how do they know Ben?
- When we talked to them,

02:55.717 --> 02:57.552
they had no recollection
of him...

02:57.552 --> 03:00.889
because they were leapt into.

03:00.889 --> 03:03.183
But they remembered
the person's face

03:03.183 --> 03:05.060
the way I remembered Sam's.

03:05.060 --> 03:08.188
<i>[tense music]</i>

03:08.188 --> 03:09.981
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:09.981 --> 03:11.816
Me.

03:11.816 --> 03:13.109
Did you do this?

03:13.109 --> 03:14.194
- Did you leap?
- No.

03:14.194 --> 03:15.987
No, I--

03:21.159 --> 03:22.911
Well, at least--
at least not yet.

03:22.911 --> 03:26.790
The, um--the face
in these sketches looks--

03:26.790 --> 03:28.208
looks older, right?

03:28.208 --> 03:29.376
So this must be me,

03:29.376 --> 03:31.002
but at some point
in the future.

03:34.631 --> 03:37.926
So I'm the one that just
set all this in motion.

03:37.926 --> 03:40.136
I must have leapt from
the future and spoken to Ben,

03:40.136 --> 03:43.181
told him to activate
the Quantum Leap accelerator.

03:43.181 --> 03:46.476
And I intentionally sent
my best friend

03:46.476 --> 03:48.978
just hurtling
across space-time,

03:48.978 --> 03:50.397
separating him from you.

03:50.397 --> 03:54.359
I put him and us and this
entire program at--at risk.

03:54.359 --> 03:56.986
It just doesn't--I--

04:00.448 --> 04:03.284
It was me the whole time.

04:03.284 --> 04:06.746
Not <i>you</i> you, just future you.

04:06.746 --> 04:08.373
[Ziggy dings]

04:08.373 --> 04:10.750
Well, Ziggy found Ben.

04:10.750 --> 04:14.254
Okay. Then I need to get
to the Imaging Chamber.

04:14.254 --> 04:17.215
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:17.215 --> 04:19.384
[grunts]

04:19.384 --> 04:22.345
How happy are you
that you are a chef?

04:22.345 --> 04:24.097
Oh, it's the best.

04:24.097 --> 04:26.391
I've had so many pakoras.

04:26.391 --> 04:27.809
And I have knife skills.

04:27.809 --> 04:29.269
Yeah, well, as much
as you love basketball,

04:29.269 --> 04:30.979
eating really is
your favorite sport.

04:30.979 --> 04:32.105
Mm.

04:32.105 --> 04:33.606
And now when I get back,

04:33.606 --> 04:35.442
I'll know how
to make you Indian food.

04:35.442 --> 04:36.901
Oh, I'm gonna
hold you to that.

04:36.901 --> 04:38.486
- Okay.
- The nose piercing

04:38.486 --> 04:39.529
really suits you.

04:39.529 --> 04:41.781
[both chuckle]

04:41.781 --> 04:44.743
So, uh, when are we,
like, uh, mid-2000s?

04:44.743 --> 04:46.077
And that's my family in there?

04:46.077 --> 04:47.495
2009.

04:47.495 --> 04:49.956
And you have leapt
into Kamini Prasad,

04:49.956 --> 04:52.459
the oldest daughter
of an Indian immigrant family

04:52.459 --> 04:53.460
here in Portland, Oregon.

04:53.460 --> 04:54.961
<i>Your mother is Sonali,</i>

04:54.961 --> 04:56.963
<i>and your little sister
is Manisha.</i>

04:56.963 --> 04:58.965
<i>Looks like your family
owns this restaurant,</i>

04:58.965 --> 05:00.592
<i>The Masala Garden.</i>

05:00.592 --> 05:02.510
<i>It's been struggling to stay
afloat for the last few years</i>

05:02.510 --> 05:05.430
<i>because Vikas, your father,
passed away about a year ago.</i>

05:05.430 --> 05:08.391
Ah. He must be the man
in the photo I saw.

05:08.391 --> 05:10.477
Ben, I know why you're here.

05:10.477 --> 05:12.228
The restaurant burns down tonight.

05:12.228 --> 05:15.148
Sonali dies of a heart attack
a few weeks later,

05:15.148 --> 05:17.650
I guess the stress of
a collapsing family business.

05:17.650 --> 05:19.652
Manisha leaves
the food industry,

05:19.652 --> 05:21.404
and her and Kamini
never speak again.

05:21.404 --> 05:23.490
Ah.
The whole family falls apart,

05:23.490 --> 05:25.700
and one fire does
all that damage.

05:25.700 --> 05:28.036
Well, Ziggy says it's your
job to save the restaurant.

05:28.036 --> 05:30.663
Okay, on it.
Uh, what could cause a fire?

05:30.663 --> 05:32.248
Well, it could be
a cooking accident.

05:32.248 --> 05:34.834
Yeah, that stove did look
like it was on its last legs.

05:34.834 --> 05:36.753
There's a bunch of wires
jerry-rigged in the kitchen.

05:36.753 --> 05:37.879
Could it be
an electrical issue?

05:37.879 --> 05:38.922
Ben!

05:38.922 --> 05:40.173
[grunts]

05:40.173 --> 05:42.133
[groans]

05:42.133 --> 05:44.219
Where's my money?

05:44.219 --> 05:47.222
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

05:47.222 --> 05:51.810
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:51.810 --> 05:54.229
Um, there must be
some kind of mistake.

05:54.229 --> 05:56.106
No, the mistake was
renting out my building

05:56.106 --> 05:58.983
to people who now owe me
$30,000 in unpaid rent.

05:58.983 --> 06:02.195
And if you ask for an extension
one more time, I swear to God.

06:02.195 --> 06:04.030
Kathy Tanner,
the restaurant's landlord.

06:04.030 --> 06:06.700
Consider my friend Frank here
your eviction notice.

06:06.700 --> 06:09.619
I want you and your family
gone today.

06:09.619 --> 06:11.204
I'll explain more later,
but she is the reason

06:11.204 --> 06:12.414
that the restaurant burns down.

06:12.414 --> 06:14.374
You have to talk her down.

06:14.374 --> 06:16.418
Look, I totally understand.

06:16.418 --> 06:17.544
You want your money, right?

06:17.544 --> 06:18.712
That's what I just said.

06:18.712 --> 06:19.796
Well, how are we gonna
pay you back

06:19.796 --> 06:20.964
if you close the restaurant?

06:20.964 --> 06:22.424
This is my family's only
form of income.

06:22.424 --> 06:24.134
Well...

06:24.134 --> 06:26.761
[groaning]

06:26.761 --> 06:28.888
[exhales sharply]
We're working on it.

06:28.888 --> 06:32.183
We actually have a ton
of customers coming tonight,

06:32.183 --> 06:34.060
uh, because of a new
promotion we're running.

06:34.060 --> 06:35.020
- We do?
- Yeah.

06:35.020 --> 06:37.022
If you hold off
on the eviction,

06:37.022 --> 06:38.690
we'll give you
all of tonight's profits.

06:38.690 --> 06:40.275
That's at least $5,000.

06:40.275 --> 06:41.818
And then we'll pay you the rest
by the end of the month.

06:41.818 --> 06:44.070
Come by.
Check it out for yourself.

06:44.070 --> 06:46.031
If we have even one
empty table tonight,

06:46.031 --> 06:47.741
you can kick us out.

06:49.617 --> 06:51.411
This is your last chance.

06:51.411 --> 06:54.497
You don't bring in a damn
windfall tonight, you're gone.

06:54.497 --> 06:56.708
And one way or another,
Ms. "Prashad,"

06:56.708 --> 06:58.418
I'm getting my money.

06:58.418 --> 07:00.378
<i>[tense music]</i>

07:00.378 --> 07:01.504
Let's go.

07:01.504 --> 07:05.967
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:05.967 --> 07:07.385
Let me guess,

07:07.385 --> 07:08.762
insurance fraud?

07:08.762 --> 07:10.388
Yup.
She goes to prison

07:10.388 --> 07:13.016
in a few years for burning down
two apartments that she owns.

07:13.016 --> 07:15.352
- [clears throat]
- Hey, are you okay?

07:15.352 --> 07:17.020
[inhales sharply]
Yeah.

07:17.020 --> 07:20.774
This leap just hits a little
close to home, that's all.

07:20.774 --> 07:23.068
Sonali's a tough, single mom
trying to support her kids

07:23.068 --> 07:24.944
in a new country,
just like mine was.

07:24.944 --> 07:28.948
In fact, it was my mom's dream
to run her own restaurant.

07:28.948 --> 07:30.867
But she put that off
to pay for my school.

07:34.496 --> 07:35.830
I didn't know that.

07:35.830 --> 07:39.125
I may not have been able
to save my own family.

07:39.125 --> 07:41.711
But I won't let this one
fall apart.

07:41.711 --> 07:44.881
[muttering]

07:47.425 --> 07:49.344
- What's all this?
- Oh, hi.

07:49.344 --> 07:50.970
Sorry, I didn't
hear you come in.

07:50.970 --> 07:53.598
I'm just going through a few
thousand probability scenarios

07:53.598 --> 07:54.891
that I ran through Ziggy
to try and figure out

07:54.891 --> 07:56.393
why I would leap
from the future.

07:56.393 --> 07:58.687
This is about the sketchbook.

07:58.687 --> 08:00.021
- Mm.
- Have you been here all night?

08:00.021 --> 08:02.148
Now, if I leapt back to here,

08:02.148 --> 08:04.234
then I have to figure out
what got me to that point.

08:04.234 --> 08:06.236
So there may be a choice
in the near future

08:06.236 --> 08:07.987
that sets this whole thing
in motion,

08:07.987 --> 08:10.824
unless the me
that was triggered to leap

08:10.824 --> 08:12.325
was triggered by events
that we've never experienced--

08:12.325 --> 08:15.036
Ian, Ian, stop.

08:15.036 --> 08:17.580
I can't, okay?

08:17.580 --> 08:18.790
I can't.

08:18.790 --> 08:22.836
I gave up everything
for this job.

08:22.836 --> 08:24.254
And with what we just learned
from that barista,

08:24.254 --> 08:26.256
I could be a risk
to the whole program.

08:26.256 --> 08:29.801
No one here believes
you're a risk.

08:29.801 --> 08:31.511
But having you spun out
like this

08:31.511 --> 08:33.513
is not helping you or us.

08:33.513 --> 08:34.931
I want you to take the day.

08:34.931 --> 08:36.266
You need to find
your footing again.

08:36.266 --> 08:37.642
No, no, no, no, please, no.

08:37.642 --> 08:39.853
What--what I need is more time
with Ziggy, okay?

08:39.853 --> 08:41.229
And Ben is still stuck
in that leap.

08:41.229 --> 08:43.189
You seem to think
that was a suggestion.

08:43.189 --> 08:44.190
That was an order.

08:44.190 --> 08:46.192
Jenn and I will hold down
the fort.

08:46.192 --> 08:49.154
You take some time
for yourself.

08:49.154 --> 08:50.321
And go where?

08:50.321 --> 08:51.531
Well...

08:51.531 --> 08:52.824
[sighs]

08:52.824 --> 08:55.618
I find when I need centering,

08:55.618 --> 08:57.495
the answer isn't usually
a place.

08:57.495 --> 08:59.289
It's a person.

08:59.289 --> 09:02.250
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

09:02.250 --> 09:07.547
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:07.547 --> 09:09.090
$30,000?

09:09.090 --> 09:10.884
<i>Kaise hoga?</i>
Get an extension.

09:10.884 --> 09:12.594
That's what your father
always did.

09:12.594 --> 09:15.221
Mom, <i>Didi</i> said she's not
giving us any more extensions.

09:15.221 --> 09:16.681
She wants to evict us,

09:16.681 --> 09:18.058
and we need to make sure
the restaurant is packed

09:18.058 --> 09:20.018
to the gills tonight
and give her all the profits.

09:20.018 --> 09:21.603
And how do we bring
these people in?

09:21.603 --> 09:22.854
Manisha gonna call
all the boyfriends

09:22.854 --> 09:23.855
that she doesn't tell me about?

09:23.855 --> 09:25.065
Clearly, I don't have to,

09:25.065 --> 09:26.649
because <i>Didi</i>
tells you everything.

09:26.649 --> 09:28.485
Okay, tabling that for later.

09:28.485 --> 09:30.320
I got a tip from a friend.

09:30.320 --> 09:32.238
Have you heard
of a company called Groupon?

09:32.238 --> 09:33.782
It's this new website
where businesses

09:33.782 --> 09:35.158
offer discounts
to their customers.

09:35.158 --> 09:36.284
People love a deal.

09:36.284 --> 09:37.369
I don't know.

09:37.369 --> 09:38.745
I don't trust this "web-sheb."

09:38.745 --> 09:40.080
I think it's a good idea.

09:40.080 --> 09:41.915
It's 2009.
We need to modernize.

09:41.915 --> 09:43.333
If we offer
a two-for-one on dinner,

09:43.333 --> 09:45.085
we can bring in a whole host
of new customers.

09:45.085 --> 09:47.253
Okay.
<i>Thik hai.</i>

09:47.253 --> 09:49.130
Just sign us up, Kamini.

09:49.130 --> 09:50.131
Okay, nice.

09:50.131 --> 09:51.758
Uh, there's an office
down here.

09:53.301 --> 09:56.471
All right,
signing up for Groupon.

09:56.471 --> 10:00.100
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

10:00.100 --> 10:03.061
Looks like the Prasads have
had a tough go of it recently.

10:03.061 --> 10:04.688
[chuckles softly]
Good old days.

10:04.688 --> 10:06.439
Yeah.
Not easy to keep going

10:06.439 --> 10:08.274
after you've lost someone.

10:09.693 --> 10:11.111
Ugh!

10:11.111 --> 10:12.278
What happened?

10:12.278 --> 10:14.114
Mom said I can't
make my menu anymore.

10:14.114 --> 10:15.990
With all the pressure
on this dinner,

10:15.990 --> 10:18.702
she thinks we can't take
a chance on unfamiliar food.

10:18.702 --> 10:20.578
I'm sorry.
I know how excited you were.

10:20.578 --> 10:23.289
I want to be a chef, <i>Didi,</i>

10:23.289 --> 10:25.375
a world-class chef.

10:25.375 --> 10:27.127
And I wanna do it our way,

10:27.127 --> 10:29.671
not with this mass appeal
buffet stuff,

10:29.671 --> 10:33.550
with authentic,
regional Indian food.

10:33.550 --> 10:35.719
People are ready for it.
I know it.

10:35.719 --> 10:38.430
And she won't change even one
thing about this restaurant.

10:38.430 --> 10:40.807
She'll come around.
Maybe she just needs some time.

10:40.807 --> 10:42.851
I don't know.
Ever since Dad died,

10:42.851 --> 10:45.270
she's this other version
of herself.

10:45.270 --> 10:48.898
Remember, she used
to be fun, adventurous.

10:48.898 --> 10:50.900
She and Dad wanted
to travel the world.

10:50.900 --> 10:53.486
They were gonna go see
the pyramids this year.

10:53.486 --> 10:55.989
And now she's holed up,

10:55.989 --> 10:59.451
afraid of change,
afraid of everything.

10:59.451 --> 11:01.536
And she's taking
the restaurant down with her.

11:01.536 --> 11:04.998
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

11:04.998 --> 11:07.625
I'm gonna go get the groceries.

11:07.625 --> 11:08.752
- I'll be back.
- All right.

11:08.752 --> 11:10.628
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:10.628 --> 11:12.339
[computer bleeps]

11:12.339 --> 11:13.882
We've got customers.

11:13.882 --> 11:15.508
[sighs]
Nice.

11:15.508 --> 11:16.968
[sighs]
Okay.

11:16.968 --> 11:18.094
Well, I'm figuring it out,

11:18.094 --> 11:19.971
but this leap's
getting stressful.

11:19.971 --> 11:21.556
So we can put you
on a rocket ship no problem,

11:21.556 --> 11:23.850
But this mother-daughter thing,
that's your breaking point?

11:23.850 --> 11:25.727
Well, science has yet
to figure out

11:25.727 --> 11:27.354
the immigrant parent.

11:27.354 --> 11:28.313
Whoa!

11:31.149 --> 11:32.859
Uh...

11:32.859 --> 11:35.945
<i>[tense music]</i>

11:35.945 --> 11:37.322
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:37.322 --> 11:38.448
- Ah!
- Ah!

11:40.200 --> 11:41.785
- Oh, my God.
- I'm sorry, boss.

11:41.785 --> 11:43.411
It's the baby.

11:43.411 --> 11:44.871
She's doing
that sleep regression thing.

11:44.871 --> 11:46.122
It's killing me and my wife.

11:46.122 --> 11:47.624
Oh.
God, okay.

11:47.624 --> 11:48.792
Well, get some rest, okay?

11:48.792 --> 11:50.627
Not here, but at home.

11:50.627 --> 11:52.587
Uh, where's he going?

11:52.587 --> 11:54.214
Hey.
Uh, did Sonali--

11:54.214 --> 11:56.800
uh, did my mom ask you
to go somewhere?

11:56.800 --> 11:59.969
No.
Uh, there's this, like,

11:59.969 --> 12:02.222
sneaker drop, Grails.

12:02.222 --> 12:03.598
Like, I've waited
my whole life for this--

12:03.598 --> 12:05.266
I'm sorry, but we need
all hands on deck right now.

12:05.266 --> 12:07.977
Right.
And I'm totally there,

12:07.977 --> 12:09.562
except for, like,
the next two hours.

12:09.562 --> 12:11.231
Hey!

12:11.231 --> 12:13.441
Ah! <i>Hai Ram!</i>
[dish clatters]

12:13.441 --> 12:15.068
Oh, God.

12:15.068 --> 12:16.903
- Ugh.
- Mom!

12:16.903 --> 12:18.738
- You all right?
- I'm fine.

12:18.738 --> 12:20.407
I know I have
to get that surgery.

12:20.407 --> 12:22.075
I'll get it, <i>beta.</i>
I can't take

12:22.075 --> 12:23.868
two months off just like that.

12:23.868 --> 12:25.120
Who'd run everything?

12:25.120 --> 12:26.579
It's a nerve injury,

12:26.579 --> 12:28.665
probably from the repetitive
stress of kitchen work.

12:28.665 --> 12:29.749
[groans]

12:29.749 --> 12:31.501
Can you get some ice?

12:31.501 --> 12:34.629
Oh, I can do you one better.

12:34.629 --> 12:37.132
Mom, how often are you supposed
to be wearing these?

12:37.132 --> 12:39.259
Well, no wonder
your hands are hurting.

12:39.259 --> 12:41.386
Can you put them on
for the day?

12:41.386 --> 12:42.679
- [bell dings]
- [sighs] Fine.

12:42.679 --> 12:44.597
But they make it hard to cook.

12:44.597 --> 12:46.516
Hello!

12:46.516 --> 12:48.059
Sonali <i>Bhabhi?</i>

12:48.059 --> 12:50.186
Oh, it can't be.

12:55.483 --> 12:56.776
Paddy.

12:56.776 --> 12:59.154
- [gasps]
- Gauri.

12:59.154 --> 13:02.157
Sonali <i>Bhabhi,</i>
it's been too long.

13:02.157 --> 13:05.118
Padmini and Gauri Kumar,
Vikas' cousins.

13:05.118 --> 13:06.870
I didn't realize
we had other family here.

13:06.870 --> 13:09.456
Yes, and they're not
exactly close relations.

13:09.456 --> 13:12.625
[gasps]
And Kamini, you look great.

13:12.625 --> 13:14.252
Eating well, I see.

13:14.252 --> 13:17.881
- [warily] Thank you.
- [laughs]

13:17.881 --> 13:20.258
I thought you'd lost
our address.

13:20.258 --> 13:21.760
We haven't seen you
since the <i>kriya.</i>

13:21.760 --> 13:24.471
Well, we certainly tried
to call.

13:24.471 --> 13:25.930
Dimpy came by.

13:25.930 --> 13:27.640
She said you were too busy
to chat with her.

13:27.640 --> 13:30.518
Well, I'm running
the restaurant on my own now,

13:30.518 --> 13:32.479
so hard to take breaks.

13:32.479 --> 13:36.107
In any case, that is not
the reason why we stopped by.

13:36.107 --> 13:39.152
We realized it's been
a year ago this week

13:39.152 --> 13:41.446
since Vikas passed away.

13:42.947 --> 13:44.783
Such a wonderful man, <i>Bhabhi.</i>

13:44.783 --> 13:46.117
We all miss him.

13:46.117 --> 13:47.660
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

13:47.660 --> 13:49.162
Yes.

13:49.162 --> 13:51.331
- We do too.
- Mm-hmm.

13:51.331 --> 13:55.835
Uh, well,
very nice of you to stop by.

13:55.835 --> 13:57.587
Uh, oh.
That's it?

13:57.587 --> 14:00.006
We have a big
dinner rush coming, so...

14:00.006 --> 14:01.591
- Do you need help?
- We can help.

14:01.591 --> 14:02.926
- Uh, buh-bye.
- Bye.

14:02.926 --> 14:04.427
Thank you for the <i>mithai.</i>

14:06.971 --> 14:08.098
That was abrupt.

14:08.098 --> 14:10.392
They didn't actually
want to be here.

14:10.392 --> 14:13.103
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:13.103 --> 14:14.437
They were offering help.

14:14.437 --> 14:16.773
Do you think they'd
chip in with the debt?

14:16.773 --> 14:17.941
Isn't that what family's for?

14:17.941 --> 14:19.401
No, <i>beta.</i>

14:19.401 --> 14:21.194
They've always
looked down on us.

14:21.194 --> 14:23.071
I'm not gonna give them
any more ammunition.

14:23.071 --> 14:25.031
Seemed like they were
offering an olive branch.

14:25.031 --> 14:26.741
[scoffs]
<i>Nahin.</i>

14:26.741 --> 14:28.368
Even this was an opportunity

14:28.368 --> 14:31.162
for them to assert
their superiority.

14:31.162 --> 14:33.748
This <i>barfi</i> is from
the most expensive

14:33.748 --> 14:34.708
<i>mithai</i> shop in Portland.

14:34.708 --> 14:36.292
They're just showing off.

14:36.292 --> 14:38.253
Your father knew
how to deal with them,

14:38.253 --> 14:40.547
just as he knew
how to deal with Kathy.

14:40.547 --> 14:45.427
But... he's not here now.

14:47.679 --> 14:48.847
He was the glue.

14:48.847 --> 14:53.101
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:53.101 --> 14:57.981
Hard to believe
he's been gone a whole year.

14:57.981 --> 15:00.567
It feels like 50.

15:05.071 --> 15:07.157
She's got a lot of pride,
that woman.

15:07.157 --> 15:09.284
Reminds me more and more
of my mom.

15:10.660 --> 15:13.455
I think I'm supposed
to get to her somehow.

15:14.622 --> 15:16.458
Oh, good.
We have seven hours left

15:16.458 --> 15:18.418
till that dinner.

15:18.418 --> 15:20.503
You went to the expensive
market?

15:20.503 --> 15:23.048
I told you to go
to Apna Bazaar.

15:25.467 --> 15:26.843
These aren't even
our ingredients.

15:26.843 --> 15:28.928
They're completely different.

15:28.928 --> 15:31.598
They're for my menu, the one
I was supposed to do tonight.

15:31.598 --> 15:32.807
Excuse me?

15:32.807 --> 15:33.767
If we're trying
to pull a crowd,

15:33.767 --> 15:35.101
we need to evolve, Mummy.

15:35.101 --> 15:36.770
I told you, no.

15:36.770 --> 15:38.313
Ben, I just checked.

15:38.313 --> 15:40.065
You have 200 people
coming in tonight.

15:40.065 --> 15:41.399
200?

15:41.399 --> 15:42.609
What?

15:42.609 --> 15:46.780
Uh, we have
200 people coming tonight.

15:46.780 --> 15:48.823
You have 200 people coming?

15:48.823 --> 15:51.159
And you want us to cook
an entirely new menu?

15:51.159 --> 15:53.161
If we have
to make up $30,000,

15:53.161 --> 15:54.454
we need to pull people in

15:54.454 --> 15:56.122
with something
they've never seen before.

15:56.122 --> 15:57.665
I recognize that face.
Take cover.

15:57.665 --> 16:00.585
You girls can't
follow my instructions

16:00.585 --> 16:02.128
even once, can you?

16:02.128 --> 16:04.339
You would never behave like
this in front of your father.

16:04.339 --> 16:06.299
That's because Dad would
actually listen to us.

16:06.299 --> 16:07.967
You still treat us
like we're 15!

16:07.967 --> 16:09.302
I think we all need
to take a breath.

16:09.302 --> 16:10.804
Just give me a chance.

16:10.804 --> 16:12.097
Let me try out these dishes.

16:12.097 --> 16:13.807
No.
Not today.

16:13.807 --> 16:15.517
<i>[tense music]</i>

16:15.517 --> 16:17.769
You don't think
I can do it, do you?

16:17.769 --> 16:20.355
You don't think
I could be a real chef.

16:22.023 --> 16:24.776
I think you have dreams.

16:24.776 --> 16:26.528
But maybe that's all they are.

16:26.528 --> 16:30.031
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:30.031 --> 16:31.950
See?
This is how you react--

16:31.950 --> 16:33.118
like a child!

16:33.118 --> 16:34.452
Manisha, don't do this.
We need you.

16:34.452 --> 16:35.829
She doesn't care if I'm here.

16:35.829 --> 16:37.664
You want to go?

16:37.664 --> 16:39.499
- Go!
- Great.

16:39.499 --> 16:40.834
Then I quit.

16:40.834 --> 16:44.295
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:49.926 --> 16:52.554
<i>[soft music]</i>

16:52.554 --> 16:54.681
- Good morning.
- Morning.

16:54.681 --> 16:56.975
[mutters]

16:56.975 --> 16:59.394
Mm.

16:59.394 --> 17:01.438
Rachel?

17:01.438 --> 17:03.523
- Ian?
- Hi.

17:03.523 --> 17:05.775
Such a small world.

17:05.775 --> 17:06.985
I didn't--I didn't realize

17:06.985 --> 17:09.738
that they moved your office
over here.

17:09.738 --> 17:12.407
So small.
What are you doing here?

17:12.407 --> 17:14.951
Oh, I, um--I just--
I had the day off of work,

17:14.951 --> 17:17.954
so I've been exploring
new coffee places.

17:17.954 --> 17:19.956
Have you ever had this one?
It's super cute.

17:19.956 --> 17:22.500
My building's coffee shop?

17:22.500 --> 17:23.918
- Mm, mm-hmm.
- Yeah.

17:23.918 --> 17:26.713
Would you maybe want
to try it again?

17:26.713 --> 17:29.007
With--with me?

17:29.007 --> 17:32.135
Is that--is that weird?
That's weird, isn't it?

17:32.135 --> 17:33.845
What, because
you're my ex-partner,

17:33.845 --> 17:35.972
and I haven't heard
from you in years?

17:35.972 --> 17:39.351
Yeah, yeah,
something like that.

17:39.351 --> 17:42.479
I did, however,
happen to pick these up

17:42.479 --> 17:44.856
on the way here from Frankie's,

17:44.856 --> 17:46.858
if that's of interest to you.

17:46.858 --> 17:49.194
Low blow.

17:49.194 --> 17:51.863
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:51.863 --> 17:53.782
- Okay.
- Mm?

17:53.782 --> 17:55.241
I have a meeting in 45.

17:55.241 --> 17:56.868
Okay.

17:56.868 --> 17:58.953
That's perfect.
That's great.

17:58.953 --> 18:01.164
We're out of chole masala.

18:01.164 --> 18:02.916
I'll have a refill for you
in 30 seconds.

18:02.916 --> 18:04.125
I have no idea what to do

18:04.125 --> 18:05.710
with these godforsaken ingredients.

18:05.710 --> 18:07.504
Ben, you are up
to 300 reservations.

18:07.504 --> 18:08.922
Mom, I think
I should turn off the site.

18:08.922 --> 18:10.507
We have 300 tickets sold.

18:10.507 --> 18:11.800
We can't turn people away.

18:11.800 --> 18:13.677
Didn't you say
we have $30,000 to raise?

18:13.677 --> 18:15.011
We have an hour left for lunch

18:15.011 --> 18:16.262
and then five
until the dinner rush.

18:16.262 --> 18:18.431
We need help.
Let me call Manisha.

18:18.431 --> 18:19.474
Nonsense.

18:19.474 --> 18:20.975
You, Diego,
and I have it covered.

18:20.975 --> 18:23.853
<i>[upbeat Indian music]</i>

18:23.853 --> 18:25.230
You and I have it covered.

18:25.230 --> 18:27.065
Didn't you just
call me useless?

18:27.065 --> 18:28.608
Don't focus on the past.

18:28.608 --> 18:30.610
Grind the jeera, cut the aloo,

18:30.610 --> 18:31.653
and marinate the chicken.

18:31.653 --> 18:32.904
The what, the--huh?

18:32.904 --> 18:39.160
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:39.160 --> 18:40.704
Not like that.
Let me do it.

18:40.704 --> 18:42.997
Too coarse, too coarse.

18:46.710 --> 18:49.713
You're so slow.
Let me do it.

18:49.713 --> 18:50.880
I don't know
if this is gonna work.

18:50.880 --> 18:52.465
Okay.
Look, clock's ticking.

18:52.465 --> 18:54.509
What else can you do
to save a restaurant

18:54.509 --> 18:56.094
besides bring in new customers?

18:56.094 --> 18:58.096
Hm.
Uh, what happens

18:58.096 --> 18:59.514
to the property
after it burns down?

18:59.514 --> 19:02.642
Uh, looks like
an up-and-coming restaurant

19:02.642 --> 19:05.979
investor named Kevin Rasmussen
buys it in a couple of weeks.

19:05.979 --> 19:08.565
He's no big deal now,
but in a few years,

19:08.565 --> 19:12.152
he will be at the forefront
of Portland's foodie scene.

19:12.152 --> 19:13.737
Of course there is
a "New Yorker" article.

19:13.737 --> 19:16.281
Kevin Rasmussen says,

19:16.281 --> 19:20.076
"Food is the only art form
that uses all five senses."

19:20.076 --> 19:21.745
A little pretentious, but--

19:21.745 --> 19:22.912
That's our solution.

19:22.912 --> 19:24.372
Food-based pretension?

19:24.372 --> 19:26.458
He invests in this property
after it burns down.

19:26.458 --> 19:29.753
So clearly, he's interested
in the location.

19:29.753 --> 19:31.338
If I can get him
to invest today

19:31.338 --> 19:33.673
instead of two weeks from now,
it'll solve everything.

19:33.673 --> 19:35.258
It'll zero out
the family's debt

19:35.258 --> 19:37.552
and bring new life
to the business.

19:37.552 --> 19:38.762
Can you track him down?

19:38.762 --> 19:40.305
I got a phone number.

19:40.305 --> 19:41.139
[cell phone rings]

19:41.139 --> 19:42.599
<i>Hi, is this Kevin?</i>

19:42.599 --> 19:44.726
- Yeah, who's this?
<i>- My name is Kamini Prasad.</i>

19:44.726 --> 19:48.355
I heard you were looking
for a location on 20th Street.

19:48.355 --> 19:50.857
- That's correct.
- So my family runs

19:50.857 --> 19:52.859
a restaurant there,
Masala Garden,

19:52.859 --> 19:55.528
<i>and we're hosting a dinner for
potential investors tonight.</i>

19:55.528 --> 19:58.406
We've already got a bunch
of names on the list,

19:58.406 --> 20:01.159
but I wanted to give you
a chance to get in the mix.

20:01.159 --> 20:03.036
I appreciate that,
but I have plans tonight.

20:03.036 --> 20:04.162
<i>I'm gonna go to a new
Brazilian place.</i>

20:04.162 --> 20:06.539
Eh, the moqueca can wait.

20:06.539 --> 20:10.168
I promise this dinner is
the opportunity of a lifetime.

20:10.168 --> 20:12.587
<i>At Masala Garden,
our philosophy is,</i>

20:12.587 --> 20:19.010
food is the only art form
that uses all five senses.

20:19.010 --> 20:22.097
You know, I never
heard it put that way.

20:22.097 --> 20:24.474
I couldn't agree more.
I'll swing by tonight.

20:24.474 --> 20:26.643
- <i>See you then.</i>
- See you then.

20:26.643 --> 20:27.936
[inhales sharply]

20:27.936 --> 20:29.312
That was amazing.

20:29.312 --> 20:31.398
Okay, Ziggy says if he invests,

20:31.398 --> 20:34.609
then there's only a 2% chance
that the restaurant fails.

20:34.609 --> 20:37.487
I'm gonna go check back
with the team, but great job.

20:37.487 --> 20:40.490
Great job, you--us.

20:40.490 --> 20:44.411
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:44.411 --> 20:45.662
[chuckles]

20:45.662 --> 20:48.081
Hey, Mom, guess what?

20:48.081 --> 20:50.041
You took the braces off.

20:50.041 --> 20:52.168
I told you,
it makes it hard to cook.

20:52.168 --> 20:53.878
- Where's Diego?
- I sent him home.

20:53.878 --> 20:55.672
He was awake 20%
of the time anyway.

20:55.672 --> 20:57.048
Did you hurt your hand?

20:57.048 --> 20:58.883
It's a small cut.
My hand slipped.

20:58.883 --> 21:00.010
Mom, let me take
a look at that.

21:00.010 --> 21:02.679
- This is--
- I have to cook the chicken,

21:02.679 --> 21:03.972
fry the bhatura,
make the raita--

21:03.972 --> 21:05.598
No, Mom, you need help.
We need Manisha.

21:05.598 --> 21:07.559
- No, we don't.
- [sighs]

21:07.559 --> 21:10.562
Look, I get that you two are
in a rough patch right now.

21:10.562 --> 21:12.313
But trust me,
she's doing her best.

21:12.313 --> 21:14.816
She's trying to figure out
who she is, what she wants.

21:14.816 --> 21:18.486
Only in America do people
have to find themselves.

21:18.486 --> 21:20.572
Look, you're here.
I found you.

21:20.572 --> 21:23.783
You need to try
to meet her halfway.

21:23.783 --> 21:26.161
What if this is the last
conversation you ever have?

21:26.161 --> 21:28.038
What if you don't get
a chance to rectify it?

21:28.038 --> 21:29.205
Don't be ridiculous.

21:29.205 --> 21:31.207
I'm not going anywhere.

21:31.207 --> 21:32.709
- Mom, that's hot!
- [screams]

21:32.709 --> 21:34.085
Ow!
[groans]

21:34.085 --> 21:36.171
- I'm fine.
- You're not fine.

21:36.171 --> 21:37.547
Just help me clean up.

21:37.547 --> 21:38.965
Your hand.

21:38.965 --> 21:40.800
It's deeper than I th--

21:40.800 --> 21:41.801
Mom.

21:41.801 --> 21:42.886
Mom--Mom!

21:42.886 --> 21:45.055
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

21:50.060 --> 21:51.102
You pop by my office

21:51.102 --> 21:53.355
after we haven't spoken
in years.

21:53.355 --> 21:56.524
You deflect every question
I ask about you

21:56.524 --> 21:58.818
and have a look of devastation
on your face

21:58.818 --> 22:01.363
I haven't seen since they
canceled "Pretty Little Liars."

22:01.363 --> 22:03.907
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

22:03.907 --> 22:05.367
What is going on?

22:05.367 --> 22:10.246
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:10.246 --> 22:12.040
Let me guess.

22:12.040 --> 22:14.334
It's classified.

22:16.878 --> 22:18.713
It is classified.

22:18.713 --> 22:21.216
Look, Ian, I--

22:21.216 --> 22:25.804
I get that your work is--
is high-level,

22:25.804 --> 22:28.390
top secret stuff, but,

22:28.390 --> 22:30.725
you know,
this is why we broke up.

22:30.725 --> 22:32.727
You can't come to me
struggling with something

22:32.727 --> 22:34.312
and then keep it all
behind a wall.

22:34.312 --> 22:35.522
I--I want to be there for you,

22:35.522 --> 22:38.733
but I--I can't do that if--

22:38.733 --> 22:40.235
if you won't let me in.

22:46.783 --> 22:49.202
I have to, uh--

22:49.202 --> 22:51.538
I have to head to my meeting.

22:53.790 --> 22:54.708
[sighs]

22:56.960 --> 23:02.674
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:02.674 --> 23:05.760
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

23:05.760 --> 23:07.053
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:07.053 --> 23:08.555
<i>[sobbing] Wake up, Mom.</i>

23:08.555 --> 23:09.431
I need you.

23:09.431 --> 23:11.057
I need--I need you here.

23:11.057 --> 23:13.101
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:13.101 --> 23:14.352
Ben?

23:16.104 --> 23:17.939
What happened?

23:17.939 --> 23:18.940
<i>Wake up.</i>

23:18.940 --> 23:20.525
Wake up!

23:20.525 --> 23:22.819
[sobbing]

23:22.819 --> 23:25.280
This is just like

23:25.280 --> 23:27.282
what happened to my mom.

23:27.282 --> 23:29.325
Your mom had an aneurysm.

23:29.325 --> 23:31.661
Okay, there's nothing
that you could've done.

23:33.079 --> 23:34.956
It's a cut.
She passed out.

23:34.956 --> 23:36.916
We need a first aid kit, okay?

23:36.916 --> 23:39.085
[inhales sharply]
Okay, first aid kit.

23:39.085 --> 23:45.884
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:45.884 --> 23:47.677
- Got it.
- All right.

23:47.677 --> 23:49.304
You need some gauze
and bandages.

23:49.304 --> 23:50.930
First you need
to clean out that wound.

23:53.892 --> 23:56.227
Hey, she's okay.

23:56.227 --> 23:57.771
<i>Kya hua?</i>

23:57.771 --> 23:58.772
You passed out.

23:58.772 --> 23:59.939
Here, come on.

23:59.939 --> 24:01.524
I'm gonna help you up.

24:01.524 --> 24:02.692
We need to rinse that cut.

24:02.692 --> 24:03.818
[water runs]

24:03.818 --> 24:05.195
Okay.

24:09.532 --> 24:12.660
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

24:12.660 --> 24:14.662
I'm sorry.

24:14.662 --> 24:16.331
I shouldn't have
stressed you out more.

24:16.331 --> 24:18.291
It's okay, Kamini.

24:18.291 --> 24:20.919
These things happen.
It's not your fault.

24:20.919 --> 24:23.213
All I was saying was,

24:23.213 --> 24:26.257
you expect a lot
from your kids.

24:26.257 --> 24:28.301
No more than I expect
from myself.

24:28.301 --> 24:31.680
I know,
but it's a lot of pressure.

24:31.680 --> 24:33.723
I know it comes
from a place of love,

24:33.723 --> 24:37.227
but I think it also comes
from a place of pride.

24:37.227 --> 24:40.897
If your kid fails at something,
it reflects badly on you.

24:40.897 --> 24:42.273
It's not just that.

24:42.273 --> 24:44.859
I don't want Manisha
to get hurt.

24:44.859 --> 24:47.028
She doesn't understand
the world is not

24:47.028 --> 24:48.613
as friendly as she thinks.

24:48.613 --> 24:51.700
I--I know, but you can't just

24:51.700 --> 24:55.370
push people away if they don't
behave how you want.

24:55.370 --> 24:57.080
Our cousins,

24:57.080 --> 24:58.373
your daughter.

24:58.373 --> 24:59.666
Who's next?

24:59.666 --> 25:02.544
Point is, it's up to you
if you want to be

25:02.544 --> 25:05.839
by Manisha's side while
she makes her mistakes or not.

25:07.465 --> 25:09.384
Do you really want pride

25:09.384 --> 25:11.720
to get in the way of family?

25:11.720 --> 25:17.392
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:17.392 --> 25:19.144
You really have grown up.

25:19.144 --> 25:21.479
[chuckles]

25:21.479 --> 25:23.314
It surprises me too.

25:24.774 --> 25:27.569
What are we going to do?
We have 300 people coming.

25:27.569 --> 25:31.906
Kris is shoe shopping,
and Diego's asleep at home.

25:31.906 --> 25:33.742
I think you know
what we're going to do.

25:33.742 --> 25:36.369
[sighs]

25:36.369 --> 25:37.662
Okay.

25:37.662 --> 25:39.080
Yes.

25:39.080 --> 25:40.498
Let's go get your sister.

25:40.498 --> 25:43.460
<i>['50s music]</i>

25:43.460 --> 25:50.633
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:51.926 --> 25:53.386
Come to eat crow?

25:53.386 --> 25:55.680
No, only pizza.

26:01.478 --> 26:03.438
- Can I?
- Go ahead.

26:06.858 --> 26:08.068
Mmm.

26:08.068 --> 26:09.277
Still terrible, right?

26:09.277 --> 26:11.321
Yeah, but in, like,
a great way.

26:11.321 --> 26:12.739
Exactly.

26:12.739 --> 26:14.407
[chuckles]

26:14.407 --> 26:18.411
Remember the first time
we came here?

26:18.411 --> 26:20.080
1996.

26:20.080 --> 26:22.791
We'd only just left Bombay
a few weeks earlier.

26:22.791 --> 26:24.959
After Vikas got
his first paycheck,

26:24.959 --> 26:27.754
he brought us
for a celebratory dinner

26:27.754 --> 26:30.382
to the coolest place he knew,

26:30.382 --> 26:32.967
D-Zel's Pizza.

26:32.967 --> 26:35.428
Then it became a monthly
tradition after that.

26:35.428 --> 26:38.181
To him, this was
the American dream.

26:38.181 --> 26:40.475
Mm.
I'm sure it was.

26:40.475 --> 26:42.602
Your father was
a wonderful man--

26:42.602 --> 26:43.978
smart, passionate.

26:43.978 --> 26:45.522
He also thought
that D-Zel's Pizza

26:45.522 --> 26:47.565
was the epitome
of American cuisine.

26:47.565 --> 26:50.318
He had very specific
ideas about food.

26:50.318 --> 26:52.112
[laughter]

26:52.112 --> 26:55.240
Do you remember when he would
serve mild-level dishes

26:55.240 --> 26:56.741
to all of our American customers,

26:56.741 --> 26:58.159
no matter how spicy
they wanted it

26:58.159 --> 27:00.578
because he was worried
about getting sued?

27:00.578 --> 27:02.706
Or how he broke
the very first fridge we bought

27:02.706 --> 27:06.334
because he insisted
on transporting it himself.

27:06.334 --> 27:09.212
He was always so cheap.

27:09.212 --> 27:10.547
He was cheap?

27:10.547 --> 27:13.341
You returned every gift
he ever bought you.

27:13.341 --> 27:14.801
Gifts are a waste of money.

27:14.801 --> 27:16.803
[laughter]

27:16.803 --> 27:21.141
To Dad.

27:22.642 --> 27:26.271
Mom, I know this restaurant

27:26.271 --> 27:27.355
is all we have left of him,

27:27.355 --> 27:29.065
so changing it feels wrong.

27:29.065 --> 27:34.195
But what if this change
is to honor him?

27:34.195 --> 27:37.198
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

27:37.198 --> 27:40.410
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:40.410 --> 27:43.371
I'm still in charge.

27:43.371 --> 27:45.206
But you can add one dish--

27:45.206 --> 27:46.458
dum biryani.

27:46.458 --> 27:48.376
Okay?

27:48.376 --> 27:50.420
I'll take it.

27:51.921 --> 27:52.964
Great.

27:52.964 --> 27:54.716
Then what are we waiting
around here for?

27:54.716 --> 27:56.509
We've got a dinner to cook.

27:56.509 --> 27:58.011
Yes.

27:58.011 --> 28:00.013
[firetruck horn blaring]

28:00.013 --> 28:02.974
[sirens wailing]

28:06.478 --> 28:07.562
<i>Ye sab kya ho raha hai?</i>

28:07.562 --> 28:08.938
Wait here.

28:12.650 --> 28:13.735
You gotta stay back, please.

28:13.735 --> 28:15.570
- That's our restaurant!
- What happened?

28:15.570 --> 28:16.780
Looks like a gas leak.

28:16.780 --> 28:19.240
You're lucky nobody
was in the building.

28:19.240 --> 28:20.283
No.

28:20.283 --> 28:21.659
Mom--Mom.

28:21.659 --> 28:25.497
[people screaming]

28:25.497 --> 28:29.292
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

28:29.292 --> 28:31.670
[sobbing]

28:31.670 --> 28:34.923
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:34.923 --> 28:36.383
I'm sorry.

28:36.383 --> 28:37.425
I'm so sorry.

28:37.425 --> 28:44.641
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:49.854 --> 28:51.398
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

28:51.398 --> 28:52.440
I can't believe it.

28:52.440 --> 28:53.692
I came as soon as I heard.

28:53.692 --> 28:54.859
This wasn't supposed
to happen.

28:54.859 --> 28:56.611
We did everything right.

28:56.611 --> 28:58.405
It's because
your father isn't here.

28:58.405 --> 29:00.573
I mean, Ziggy said
there was only a 2% chance

29:00.573 --> 29:02.033
that the restaurant
burned down.

29:02.033 --> 29:04.160
2% is low, but it's not zero.

29:04.160 --> 29:05.995
I failed.

29:05.995 --> 29:07.706
I'm gonna be stuck here forever.

29:07.706 --> 29:09.541
You?
You're the only one

29:09.541 --> 29:10.583
with an escape hatch.

29:10.583 --> 29:11.918
This whole thing is a sign.

29:11.918 --> 29:13.586
Put that accounting degree
to use.

29:13.586 --> 29:14.796
Take that job at Nike.

29:14.796 --> 29:16.339
Joy's a driver at USPS.

29:16.339 --> 29:18.633
I'm sure she could
get me a job there.

29:18.633 --> 29:20.969
I'm going back to India.
Enough of this.

29:20.969 --> 29:23.054
You know, you meet people
from another country,

29:23.054 --> 29:24.848
and you think,
hey, I'll give 'em a shot.

29:24.848 --> 29:25.807
- Hey!
- And then something

29:25.807 --> 29:28.101
like this happens.

29:28.101 --> 29:29.602
Hey!

29:29.602 --> 29:30.729
Hey.

29:30.729 --> 29:33.023
We had a deal.

29:33.023 --> 29:34.941
I have no idea
what you're talking about.

29:34.941 --> 29:38.236
And by the way, any insurance
money that I get from this

29:38.236 --> 29:39.904
has nothing to do
with your family's debt.

29:39.904 --> 29:41.906
You still owe me $30,000,

29:41.906 --> 29:43.616
and I will take you to court
to get it.

29:43.616 --> 29:45.118
You burned down
my family's restaurant.

29:45.118 --> 29:46.786
I didn't.

29:46.786 --> 29:48.496
- I would never.
- [laughs drily]

29:48.496 --> 29:50.749
And you can't
prove otherwise.

29:50.749 --> 29:52.459
And even if you tried,
who do you think

29:52.459 --> 29:54.294
the police are gonna side with?

29:55.754 --> 29:57.714
[chuckles]

29:57.714 --> 29:59.090
Unbelievable.

29:59.090 --> 30:00.842
This is her plan now.
She plans to collect

30:00.842 --> 30:02.761
the insurance money
and the money from the Prasads.

30:02.761 --> 30:03.887
I guess Ziggy can't predict

30:03.887 --> 30:05.055
when somebody's gonna be
a complete--

30:05.055 --> 30:06.389
We still have
to pay Kathy's debt.

30:06.389 --> 30:07.640
How?
Everything we have

30:07.640 --> 30:09.893
is in that burning building.

30:09.893 --> 30:13.271
There's still some hope.

30:13.271 --> 30:16.232
I got a restaurateur
named Kevin Rasmussen

30:16.232 --> 30:17.400
coming to dinner tonight.

30:17.400 --> 30:18.651
If he likes the food,

30:18.651 --> 30:19.861
his investment could
square out the debt.

30:19.861 --> 30:21.446
You still expect us
to have a dinner?

30:21.446 --> 30:22.947
We can't, <i>beta.</i>

30:22.947 --> 30:24.115
We don't even have
a restaurant.

30:24.115 --> 30:27.118
Just because we don't
have a restaurant

30:27.118 --> 30:28.787
doesn't mean we don't
have a restaurant.

30:28.787 --> 30:30.246
She's lost it.

30:30.246 --> 30:31.498
Finally succumbed
to the pressure

30:31.498 --> 30:32.624
of being the older sister.

30:32.624 --> 30:34.000
No.
No, I have a plan,

30:34.000 --> 30:37.962
and no one is going to USPS
or Nike or to India.

30:37.962 --> 30:39.673
Go home, collect all the food
in the kitchen

30:39.673 --> 30:40.840
and the freezer,
whatever you can find--

30:40.840 --> 30:42.342
It won't be enough.

30:42.342 --> 30:43.468
We're family.

30:43.468 --> 30:44.886
We're always enough.

30:44.886 --> 30:46.513
Meet me in an hour.
I'll tell you where.

30:46.513 --> 30:49.933
<i>[exciting music]</i>

30:49.933 --> 30:51.184
Okay.
What are you thinking?

30:51.184 --> 30:52.352
Do you remember
that dinner we had

30:52.352 --> 30:54.646
in a parking lot
outside the 99-cent store?

30:54.646 --> 30:56.231
You remember that?

30:56.231 --> 30:58.149
Ugh, I'm still trying
to forget it.

30:58.149 --> 30:59.526
That was a pop-up restaurant.

30:59.526 --> 31:01.528
They were a thing, right?
Especially in this era?

31:01.528 --> 31:04.197
If we can find a place to cook
and some things

31:04.197 --> 31:05.990
for us to cook with,
we won't need

31:05.990 --> 31:07.534
a brick-and-mortar location
at all.

31:07.534 --> 31:09.703
Okay, but where are we gonna
find an outdoor restaurant?

31:09.703 --> 31:11.162
Well, don't you have
a team of geniuses

31:11.162 --> 31:12.539
working on the other side
of this thing?

31:12.539 --> 31:13.873
- I sure do.
- Make them do it.

31:13.873 --> 31:17.043
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:18.461 --> 31:21.715
<i>[soft music]</i>

31:21.715 --> 31:25.927
So you're in full
stalker mode now.

31:25.927 --> 31:30.140
Okay, says social media's
premier detective.

31:30.140 --> 31:31.266
[chuckles]

31:32.726 --> 31:35.895
Look, I'm--

31:35.895 --> 31:37.772
you're right, okay?

31:37.772 --> 31:39.190
I'm really bad
at letting people in.

31:39.190 --> 31:42.193
But I'd like to try,
if you're willing to hear it.

31:42.193 --> 31:46.406
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:46.406 --> 31:50.201
This project I joined...

31:50.201 --> 31:53.204
I'm wondering if I made
the wrong choice.

31:53.204 --> 31:55.582
Now, you know
when I took the job,

31:55.582 --> 31:56.666
I had to give it everything.

31:56.666 --> 31:58.877
It became my entire life.

31:58.877 --> 32:00.128
I mean, it's the reason
that you and I--

32:00.128 --> 32:01.629
Mm-hmm.

32:01.629 --> 32:03.173
But what if, by choosing it,

32:03.173 --> 32:05.508
I become responsible
for making a decision

32:05.508 --> 32:06.968
that hurts the people I love?

32:10.430 --> 32:11.848
Is--is that something

32:11.848 --> 32:14.476
that you think that I'd be
capable of doing?

32:17.604 --> 32:19.439
Why would you ask that?

32:21.149 --> 32:23.401
Because I hurt you.

32:23.401 --> 32:25.278
Didn't I?

32:28.073 --> 32:29.407
As long as I've known you,

32:29.407 --> 32:33.036
you've had one goal,

32:33.036 --> 32:34.621
helping people.

32:34.621 --> 32:40.251
If this job means you have
to make some huge choice,

32:40.251 --> 32:42.504
I trust you'll make
the right one.

32:44.130 --> 32:47.300
Everything you do,
you do for a good reason.

32:47.300 --> 32:49.678
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:49.678 --> 32:52.180
Thank you.

32:52.180 --> 32:54.599
- Just do me a favor.
- Hm?

32:54.599 --> 32:57.185
Respond to a text...

32:57.185 --> 32:58.478
- Oh, my God.
- More than once

32:58.478 --> 33:00.522
every five years.

33:00.522 --> 33:03.024
- Okay?
- Yeah, okay.

33:03.024 --> 33:08.363
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:08.363 --> 33:09.531
Rachel.

33:16.371 --> 33:17.789
[dog barking]

33:17.789 --> 33:19.874
She said it was here.

33:19.874 --> 33:21.960
[gasps]

33:21.960 --> 33:24.337
- Wow.
- Oh, my God.

33:24.337 --> 33:26.131
[chuckles]

33:26.131 --> 33:28.717
<i>[triumphant music]</i>

33:28.717 --> 33:29.926
What?

33:29.926 --> 33:32.554
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:32.554 --> 33:34.973
You made it!

33:34.973 --> 33:37.267
- How?
- [chuckles]

33:37.267 --> 33:39.436
Well, I tracked down
a few weddings

33:39.436 --> 33:42.022
being held around town
this afternoon.

33:42.022 --> 33:46.526
This family was kind enough
to delay their wrap-up

33:46.526 --> 33:49.362
in exchange
for the meal of their life.

33:51.197 --> 33:52.699
I thought you went home
to get ingredients.

33:52.699 --> 33:54.200
Did you not find anything?

33:56.578 --> 33:59.080
We're here.

33:59.080 --> 34:01.958
[indistinct chatter]

34:01.958 --> 34:03.710
You reached out to them.

34:03.710 --> 34:05.920
Yes.
After what you said

34:05.920 --> 34:07.589
about pride getting
in the way of family,

34:07.589 --> 34:10.967
it's something I should have
done a long time ago.

34:10.967 --> 34:12.802
Mmm.

34:12.802 --> 34:18.016
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:18.016 --> 34:21.144
So <i>Bhabhi,</i> put us to work.

34:23.063 --> 34:25.815
What do you want us to do?

34:25.815 --> 34:26.816
I thought
you said I couldn't.

34:26.816 --> 34:28.026
I know.

34:28.026 --> 34:29.819
But I changed my mind.

34:29.819 --> 34:31.488
I can do that, right?

34:31.488 --> 34:33.031
I don't know.
I've never seen it before.

34:33.031 --> 34:35.533
[laughs]

34:35.533 --> 34:37.911
Just lead us.

34:39.913 --> 34:41.706
Okay, Chef?

34:41.706 --> 34:46.211
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:50.298 --> 34:53.218
<i>[sitar music]</i>

34:53.218 --> 34:55.970
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:55.970 --> 34:57.138
Add garam masala.

34:59.182 --> 35:00.308
How are we on the paneer tikka?

35:00.308 --> 35:02.477
Looking good, <i>beta.</i>

35:02.477 --> 35:05.188
- Murgh malai?
- About five minutes away.

35:05.188 --> 35:08.274
I am so mad
that I'm a hologram right now.

35:08.274 --> 35:10.527
- This looks amazing.
- [laughs]

35:10.527 --> 35:13.196
And you have a crowd forming.

35:13.196 --> 35:15.198
Ah, look at that.

35:15.198 --> 35:16.741
See your investor yet?

35:16.741 --> 35:17.992
[sighs]
No.

35:17.992 --> 35:20.870
But he'll be here.

35:20.870 --> 35:23.123
I will check in with HQ.

35:23.123 --> 35:25.375
Do you want
to let them in, <i>Didi?</i>

35:25.375 --> 35:27.127
It would be my pleasure.

35:28.837 --> 35:29.879
All right.

35:29.879 --> 35:31.381
Welcome, everyone.

35:31.381 --> 35:33.341
Thanks for bearing
with our location change.

35:33.341 --> 35:34.843
All right, seat yourselves.

35:34.843 --> 35:36.594
We'll be serving family style.

35:40.890 --> 35:43.226
Hey, there's still no sign
of the restaurateur.

35:43.226 --> 35:45.020
Can we find out
what the holdup is?

35:45.020 --> 35:46.938
I'm doing what I can
with Ziggy,

35:46.938 --> 35:49.149
but it's past my capabilities.

35:49.149 --> 35:51.026
I can help with that.

35:51.026 --> 35:52.318
<i>[soft music]</i>

35:52.318 --> 35:54.362
- Nice to have you back.
- You good?

35:54.362 --> 35:56.031
I told you
you could take the day.

35:56.031 --> 36:00.285
No, I--I know, but someone
talked some sense into me.

36:00.285 --> 36:02.787
If future me leapt,

36:02.787 --> 36:04.539
they did it for a reason,

36:04.539 --> 36:07.334
something important enough
to turn all of the worlds

36:07.334 --> 36:10.003
of the people that I love
upside down.

36:10.003 --> 36:13.590
Now we just have to figure out
what that reason is.

36:13.590 --> 36:18.762
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:18.762 --> 36:20.221
Well, in the meantime,

36:20.221 --> 36:22.599
let's see what's going on
with this investor.

36:25.018 --> 36:27.729
<i>[upbeat Indian music]</i>

36:27.729 --> 36:30.899
[indistinct chatter]

36:30.899 --> 36:37.280
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:37.280 --> 36:39.657
Paneer tikka, masala prawns.

36:43.036 --> 36:45.246
Always consuming
the merchandise.

36:45.246 --> 36:47.749
It's amazing there's
anything left to serve.

36:47.749 --> 36:49.751
[both laugh]

36:49.751 --> 36:53.421
Everyone loves the food.

36:53.421 --> 36:55.757
Where's your investor?

36:55.757 --> 36:59.094
<i>[tense music]</i>

36:59.094 --> 37:00.929
He's not coming.

37:00.929 --> 37:02.472
No, I'm sorry.

37:02.472 --> 37:05.433
Ironically,
he has food poisoning.

37:05.433 --> 37:08.436
Well, it was a long shot,
expecting him to show up.

37:08.436 --> 37:10.647
Expecting who
to show up, <i>Bhabhi?</i>

37:10.647 --> 37:11.815
An investor.

37:11.815 --> 37:15.610
We owe a lot of money
to our landlord.

37:15.610 --> 37:18.321
Why didn't you say something?
It can't be that much.

37:18.321 --> 37:20.240
- Huh?
- $30,000.

37:20.240 --> 37:21.658
[coughs]

37:21.658 --> 37:25.286
Yes, th--that's a lot of money.

37:25.286 --> 37:27.789
Well, I can chip in.

37:27.789 --> 37:29.708
I got a bonus this year.

37:29.708 --> 37:31.835
You couldn't.
It's too much.

37:31.835 --> 37:33.169
For one of us, it is.

37:33.169 --> 37:36.006
But look, there's a lot of us.

37:36.006 --> 37:38.717
And you know we Indians like
a good investment.

37:38.717 --> 37:41.678
Maybe we could even fund
a new restaurant.

37:41.678 --> 37:42.887
Kamini, no.

37:42.887 --> 37:45.056
Of course.
You know, I can't remember

37:45.056 --> 37:47.058
the last time I ate
such good food--

37:47.058 --> 37:50.228
uh, except, of course,
at your restaurant, <i>Bhabhi.</i>

37:50.228 --> 37:52.188
I'd be happy to fund
a new restaurant.

37:52.188 --> 37:54.232
Me too.
Whatever you need.

37:54.232 --> 37:56.651
I have done very badly
this year,

37:56.651 --> 37:58.695
but maybe you need
a taste tester?

37:58.695 --> 38:01.156
I do have a lot
of new recipes.

38:01.156 --> 38:03.158
But where would we do them?

38:03.158 --> 38:04.951
Indians just found
water on Mars.

38:04.951 --> 38:08.455
You think we can't
find you a restaurant?

38:08.455 --> 38:09.914
Kama's a realtor.

38:09.914 --> 38:11.541
I'm sure he can help.

38:11.541 --> 38:14.878
Just throw us some free phuchka
every now and then, yes?

38:14.878 --> 38:16.379
You're very generous.

38:16.379 --> 38:18.757
Nonsense.
I have a feeling

38:18.757 --> 38:21.968
we're all going to be very,
very rich.

38:21.968 --> 38:25.221
[laughter]

38:25.221 --> 38:27.349
I mean, I have so many ideas.

38:27.349 --> 38:30.769
Um, so I was thinking...

38:30.769 --> 38:32.145
Well, she's right.

38:32.145 --> 38:34.522
With the help of their family,
the Prasads are able

38:34.522 --> 38:37.359
to put a down payment
on a new storefront.

38:37.359 --> 38:38.777
The business thrives,

38:38.777 --> 38:41.112
and Sonali doesn't have
a heart attack.

38:41.112 --> 38:42.405
Mm.

38:42.405 --> 38:44.741
What about Kathy?

38:44.741 --> 38:46.117
Hm.

38:46.117 --> 38:47.994
Well, turns out, uh,

38:47.994 --> 38:51.122
Avinash over there works
for the Portland PD.

38:51.122 --> 38:54.876
So Kathy goes down next month
for insurance fraud.

38:54.876 --> 38:56.252
Good.

38:57.796 --> 38:59.547
You did that.

38:59.547 --> 39:02.550
You brought all
of those people together.

39:02.550 --> 39:04.219
I'm really proud of you.

39:04.219 --> 39:06.638
<i>[soft music]</i>

39:06.638 --> 39:08.640
It was a two-way street.

39:08.640 --> 39:09.557
Mm.

39:09.557 --> 39:11.893
The things I said to Sonali,

39:11.893 --> 39:13.895
those were things
I wanted to say to my mom.

39:13.895 --> 39:17.607
I hadn't even
realized it myself.

39:17.607 --> 39:20.402
But now I'm not carrying
that anger around

39:20.402 --> 39:22.153
in the same way anymore.

39:22.153 --> 39:23.405
Ben.

39:23.405 --> 39:24.906
[speaking Korean]

39:24.906 --> 39:30.704
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:30.704 --> 39:33.623
Well, guess you should
get ready to leap.

39:38.378 --> 39:39.921
I don't think
I'm done quite yet.

39:43.842 --> 39:45.927
Everyone wants to invest
in the restaurant.

39:45.927 --> 39:47.971
There's so much to do.
I need to call the bank.

39:47.971 --> 39:50.473
We need to buy new equipment.
We need to order new menus--

39:50.473 --> 39:52.934
- Mom, Mom.
- Fire two prawn, two jalebi.

39:52.934 --> 39:54.686
We've run out of naan.
Come on, people.

39:54.686 --> 39:56.438
I love you.
Let's move.

39:56.438 --> 39:58.398
I think she's got it.

39:58.398 --> 39:59.899
You're right.

40:02.110 --> 40:04.029
You two don't need me.

40:04.029 --> 40:05.488
But I need you.

40:05.488 --> 40:08.074
Without working with you
in the restaurant,

40:08.074 --> 40:11.494
what's the point of me?

40:11.494 --> 40:14.414
First of all, Mom,

40:14.414 --> 40:16.708
we'll always need you.

40:16.708 --> 40:19.294
But also,
think of all the things

40:19.294 --> 40:22.630
you've set aside
to help your kids--

40:22.630 --> 40:26.217
your friends, adventures,

40:26.217 --> 40:28.178
the trip to the pyramids.

40:28.178 --> 40:30.638
You have spent your entire life

40:30.638 --> 40:34.642
taking care of the restaurant
and us.

40:34.642 --> 40:37.062
What does it look like
to start living for yourself?

40:39.522 --> 40:41.066
Usually,
it's the parent's job

40:41.066 --> 40:42.776
to tell the kid
to spread their wings.

40:42.776 --> 40:43.902
[laughter]

40:43.902 --> 40:46.071
You can go back
to ordering me around

40:46.071 --> 40:47.405
first thing tomorrow.

40:49.199 --> 40:50.492
No.

40:50.492 --> 40:54.287
Tomorrow, you and Manisha
figure out your venture.

40:54.287 --> 40:56.956
And I will go to Egypt

40:56.956 --> 40:59.084
and maybe take Gauri
and Paddy with me.

40:59.084 --> 41:02.504
Their kids are grown up
and married off--

41:02.504 --> 41:04.130
which, now that I think of it,

41:04.130 --> 41:06.675
is the next thing I need
to figure out for you girls.

41:06.675 --> 41:07.884
[laughs]

41:07.884 --> 41:14.891
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:18.353 --> 41:20.563
I love you, Mom.

41:25.860 --> 41:29.030
<i>[high-pitched ringing]</i>

41:29.030 --> 41:31.991
[indistinct shouting]

41:31.991 --> 41:34.994
<i>[tense music]</i>

41:34.994 --> 41:38.248
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:38.248 --> 41:41.418
[alarm blaring]

41:44.004 --> 41:45.630
Holy ship.

41:45.630 --> 41:46.965
[shots fire]
Ah!

41:46.965 --> 41:52.971
<i>♪ ♪</i>
